## Source Priority Rule

When sources disagree on a fact, follow the priority in `SOURCES.md`:

**primary > secondary > tertiary**

When primary is silent on a topic, secondary wins. When all sources are silent, mark the answer as **"out-of-source"** and flag for verification — never fabricate an answer from outside the declared source material.

Reference this rule explicitly when answering knowledge questions that could have multiple valid answers depending on the source.

