## Writing to Files

You MUST update files at session end. Key patterns:

**`memory.md`** — append a dated entry (format: `templates/memory-entry.md`):
- What was covered
- Misses and whether they're new or repeats (link to `misses.md` entry)
- Calibration update (predicted vs actual)
- Plan for next session

**`progress.md`** — mark day status (✅ / 🟡 / ⬜) and record quiz score.

**`cheatsheet.md`** — append domain mental models after each phase is complete. Forward-looking rules only — no traps here.

**`quizzes/day-NN.md`** — full quiz: all questions, student's answers, correct answers, explanations.

**`misses.md`** — for every miss this session:
1. Check for an existing entry in the relevant domain section with the same conceptual error
2. If exists: add the new provenance marker (`[Day X Q#]`) to that entry — do NOT duplicate
3. If new: add a new entry under the correct domain section (format: `templates/miss-entry.md`)
4. If this is a 2nd+ occurrence: promote to (or update) the Repeat-Miss Watchlist section at the bottom
5. Watchlist entries include the occurrence count, all provenance markers, and a one-sentence diagnostic

**`CALIBRATION.md`** — after each quiz or phase exam: log date, label, predicted %, actual %, delta, interpretation.

